Author : Olivier Koch, olivier@olivierkoch.org

Date : July 2016

Dependencies
------------------------------------------

Pillow
python-tk
python-imaging-tk
xautomation


Allowing user to write to /dev/uinput
------------------------------------------
create a new group uinput:
sudo groupadd -f uinput
add user to group:
sudo gpasswd -a <username> uinput
reboot!

create new udev rule:
create a file named /etc/udev/rules.d/99-input.rules
insert the following line
KERNEL=="uinput", GROUP="uinput", MODE="0660"
reboot!

